Others: Quincy Olivari received praise from Lakers head coach JJ Redick for his exceptional effort in the win against the Milwaukee Bucks.
Olivari scored 11 points, grabbed 5 rebounds, and handed out 2 assists in just 9 minutes and 24 seconds of play.
LeBron James praised Olivari, calling him 'game-changing'.
The Lakers' bench mob caught fire and helped the team regain the lead.
Olivari's explosive performance in the fourth quarter took center stage as he led the offense and carried the team.
The Lakers' next preseason matchup is against the Golden State Warriors.
